11:54 am case called. Defendant Victor H Cortez in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by Court regarding extradition request to the State of Texas. Court questions defendant-has received a copy of petition. Right to counsel addressed. Defendant requests attorney. Statement by Attorney Anderson regarding SPD representation-SPD will not appoint an attorney based on type of warrant. Court questions defendant regarding contesting extradition to Texas. Discussion between court and ADA Anderson. Court authorizes return to State of Texas-probable cause found for absconding probation in Texas. Court determines governor's warrant is not needed for extradition. Court directs defendant's return to State of Texas-no governors warrant needed. Court enters order for extradition.
from ADA Anderson Re: Necessity of going forward with Extradition Hearing - Court will address at the Extradition Hearing scheduled for June 23, 2015.

Case Called @ 3:07 PM:  Defendant Victor H Cortez in court, appearing in person without counsel.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def states he wishes to contest extradition to Texas and nw wants counsel.  He does not wish to return to Texas.  Court explains nature of charges in Texas.  Court explains Def's right to contest extradition.  If contested, Texas would need to obtain a Governor's warrant for his return.  Statement by Det. Hood - transport officer.  Officer believes that an attorney would be helpful.    Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.   Court orders Def held without bond pending futher hearing.  Extradition hearing scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 11:45 am.
